%% Diagram: Pending / active / recycle tree lifecycle
%% Type: stateDiagram
%%{init: {'htmlLabels': false}}%%
stateDiagram-v2
    direction TB
    [*] --> ActiveOnly: first frame committed<br/>(active tree displayed)
    ActiveOnly --> Committing: ProxyImpl runs<br/>ScheduledActionCommit
    Committing --> PendingPlusActive: pending tree populated<br/>active tree still displayed
    PendingPlusActive --> Rastering: TileManager schedules<br/>required tiles
    Rastering --> ActivationGated: required tiles ready
    ActivationGated --> RecyclePlusActive: pending → active swap<br/>previous active becomes recycle
    RecyclePlusActive --> Committing: next commit reuses<br/>recycle for allocation
    Rastering --> Stalled: required tiles not ready
    Stalled --> Rastering: keep rasterizing
    Stalled --> BackPressure: next BeginMainFrame<br/>completes, NotifyReadyToCommit
    BackPressure --> ActivationGated: previous tree<br/>finally activates

    note right of PendingPlusActive
        Active tree keeps handling
        scroll, animations, input
        while pending tree rasters.
    end note
    note right of RecyclePlusActive
        Recycle tree is allocation
        cache only — never drawn.
        Mutually exclusive with
        a fresh pending tree.
    end note
